text: The next level for the site is probably to make it a destination/portal more than a tool.
Articles are the first step in that, and I’m guessing other functionality is coming to expand that too.

As for promoting yourself, that’s how you as a writer reach the next level, should you want to reach it. For every actor that gets found ordering coffee at Starbucks the other 10,000 get found grinding out auditions and work. The same is true here. You might make the next leap just because someone likes your series and approaches you for something else , but way more likely is they do it because you constantly put yourself out there.

Of the writers there is a reason DM and Dean have 500+ Twitter followers and that’s because they do the work. Jason has 5k because he does the work. Like him or not the Prof has 400k because he does the work.

I’d also suggest people find a niche and own it or have a definable persona. There’s a gazillion random edh people out there with no definable thing to set them apart (I’m probably one) but (apologies for the oversimplification) Jason is the biting finance guy, the Prof and Saff have their own schtick, Hambly is an alt right goon, Proxy Guy makes proxies, Sam does hyperspecific deep dives on stuff, etc. Being generic dude #1,329 with a generic opinion probably doesn’t get it done. And this is coming from someone who is often generic dude #1,330 so  I struggle with that one as well.
